>
<br>
I really really really think that SoE, in its desire to give people what they want, has done some catering to the lowest common denominiator here with PoP. People wanted something easy and that is what they have gotten....I understand and sympathize with the ease thing--sometimes I want something easy too--that is what twinks are for, that is what pos frogs are for. But too much of that is really boring.<br>
<br>
Regarding the flag thing, let me tell a story. When I was in my mid-thirties in Amnesty some of our members decided we all needed sebilis keys. I came and helped out a few times, the key mobs were red, it was a scary run, I wasmore interested in going to SOlB or CT, but I came and eventually I got a seb key at like level 37. Guildmates all went to seb that night--ranging in levels I think from about 35 to 50. I went to sleep.<br>
<br>
They got their asses handed to them, as Sebilis is not particularly kind to players that are levels 35 to 50--and the humiliation was pretty public, as at that time it was pretty crowded.<br>
<br>
I went to seb for the first time at about level 46.  For reasons I don't understand, someone actually gave me a group there. It totally sucked--they'd say, &quot;bard mez this&quot; and I couldnt, they'd say &quot;bard snare this&quot; and I couldnt, I died alot, and after about 30 minutes I realized I was wasting everyones time so I left and went somewhere where the mobs were blue.<br>
<br>
I went back at level 51 and dinged 52 but it was still annoying. I couldnt really perform the roles I needed to there--I didnt have the songs yet. Being somewhere where the mobs are waaay too high for you in an exp group isnt really that fun.<br>
<br>
So it will be with these PoP zones after the initial exploration phase.<br>
<br>
If the quest and raid mobs are still needed for advancement, I have alot less of an issue with it, but I still have some. Soe screwed up by not putting any straight dungeon zones in the game with PoP. Several of the flag zones---PoT, HoH, Plane of Torment, are not really &quot;great&quot; experience zones anyways. Some have argued that the straight experience is better in PoV. (I am not sure about that, but...)<br>
<br>
Soe should have put in some dungeons with good exp modifiers and spec drops that required no flags at all. It is important with EQ that everyone feels like they have something to shoot for, some goal to accomplish. Its the carrot on the stick, its the brass ring. Getting through the trials was the first pop one, then bot usually for most. Also cod---whether you quested it or killed Grummus. And so on.<br>
<br>
Giving a set of different brass rings would have been good. Taking some out of the game will probably make many people more bored.<br>
<br>
